 Madhya Pradesh. After section 30, add the following section, namely: 
 30A. Removal of difficulties .If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of this Act, the State Government may, by order, do anything, not inconsistent with the provisions of the Act, which appears to it to be necessary or expedient for the purposes of removing the difficulties.'' 
